Place oven rack in upper third of the oven. Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Line 15x10-inch baking pan with sides with parchment or foil; spray with cooking spray. Coat the chicken with the sauce and roll in crumbs mixed with salt and pepper. Place on baking pan and drizzle with butter. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until juice of chicken is clear when thickest part is cut to bone.